cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with querying and mining of time series data, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The focus on similarity measures and representation methods suggests that cs.DB (databases) and cs.IR (information retrieval) are likely sub-categories. The use of machine learning techniques for dimensionality reduction and similarity measures also suggests cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the experimental nature of the study and the use of multiple techniques suggest cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) as a possible sub-category.
